Description: Fragment of strap handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine orange-buff; much small mica. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 206, 3. G. Joehrens reports five such stamps, the illustrated one from the same die, from Miletus (Archaeologische Anzeiger 2009, 219, no. 43).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0073)
